---- MODULE Alternate ----

(***************************************************************************
Generated at Sat Oct 31 02:58:46 PDT 2009                               *)
(* This specifies a system that alternately performs two actions, which    *)
for now I will call A_0 and A_1.  It uses a variable v whose value      *)
alternates between 0 and 1, performing an A_0 action when v changes     *)
from 0 to 1, and an A_1 action when v changes from 1 to 0.              *)
***************************************************************************)
CONSTANTS   XInit,        \* The initial state predicate.                    *)
            XAct         \* An operator that asserts a change of the part x      *)
VARIABLES   v,           \* A variable representing which action is next to be  *)
             x            \* The part of the state changed by an Action_i     *)
INITIAL                    \* The initial predicate.                          *)
============= =============================================================)
Init ==        XInit(x) /\ v = 0   \* All parts have correct initial values.      *)
             /******************************/                                )
\EE           Spec                                                     :)
            **** The specification for the system we are modeling.       :*)
============================== =============================================)
INVARIANTS   XInit,        \* Initial state predicate is preserved.          *)
             /******************************/                                )
\EE           Spec /\ v = 0     The specification remains valid for all values of       :*)
            **** x and the initial value of v (which should always be 0).   :)
============================== =============================================)
TRANSITIONS XAct,        \* An operator that asserts a change in      *)
             /******************************/                                )
\EE           Spec /\ XInit(x) ==> v = (v + 1) MOD 2   The specification     :*)
            **** remains valid for all values of x and the initial value    :)*
============================== =============================================)
*)
------------------------------ ---------------------------------------      )
tla-config.cfg                                                          :*)
******************************  ************************************     :*)
[TLC]                                                                :)*
InitNext=10, Timeout=604800, Strategy=SATISFIABILITY               *)
******************************  ************************************     :*)
(Note: This is a default config file. You can modify it to your   :)*
needs by adding or removing options.)                                :)*
------------------------------ ---------------------------------------      )
